SIMPLE: throwaway
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: throwaway
<hw>throw"a*way</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>designed to be
discarded after a single use; disposable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>spoken with deliberate underemphasis; <as>as, a
<ex>throwaway</ex> line in a play</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>throwaway</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: throwaway
<hw>throw"a*way</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an advertisement
(usually printed on a page or in a leaflet) intended for wide
distribution.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> circular, handbill, bill, broadside, broadsheet,
flier, flyer</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>words spoken in a casual way with conscious
underemphasis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>throwback</ent>⟦br⟧
